class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--2"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-9b24849f" data-pf-type="Column"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-96291393--images.jpg?v=1589320244 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-96291393--images.jpg?v=1589320244 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-96291393--images.jpg?v=1589320244 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-4b4aafdc" data-pf-type="Image2"></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--10"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-849fdb21" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-e4514b4a"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-af90e451">Unfortunately, there is no such thing as a light that simulates natural sunlight. It is beyond the laws of physics to turn electricity into sunlight.</span></p></div></div></div><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-9359a8b1--African-Grey.jpg?v=1589320419 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-9359a8b1--African-Grey_800x800.jpg?v=1589320419&resized 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-9359a8b1--African-Grey_400x400.jpg?v=1589320419&resized 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-afdcb112" data-pf-type="Image2"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-59a8b184--AgnusProfile.jpg?v=1589320462 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-59a8b184--AgnusProfile_800x697.jpg?v=1589320462&resized 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-59a8b184--AgnusProfile_400x349.jpg?v=1589320462&resized 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-139359a8" data-pf-type="Image2"></div></div></div><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-02a7be83 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-2602778b" data-pf-type="Column"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-a8b184a5--3-Male-Gouldians.jpg?v=1589320514 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-a8b184a5--3-Male-Gouldians_800x815.jpg?v=1589320514&resized 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-a8b184a5--3-Male-Gouldians_400x408.jpg?v=1589320514&resized 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-be83731c" data-pf-type="Image2"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-b5a17a97"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-0c08b5a1">Here are some facts that are proven and indisputable.</span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-f478c200" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-3224f478"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-aa773224">THE MOST AFFECTIVE HEALTH BENIFIT FROM ARTIFICIAL LIGHT IS PHOTOPERIOD</span></h3></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-0dd702a7" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-ce31ff7a"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-cdd4786c">Photoperiod is just a fancy word for how many hours per day a bird is exposed to light, even artificial light. Photoperiod is what triggers many hormones in birds, therefore incorrect or inconsistent photoperiod can cause many problems. </span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-ff7afb88"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-b2ca8e44">“If there is one single positive change that pet bird owners can make, <br>it is returning the bird to a regularly recurring photoperiod.”</span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-eabbbd17"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-db7deabb"> Dr. Fern Van Sant DMV San Jose, CA</span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-133ac3f0"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-837c133a">Adding a light like M&M’s Pet Light to your bird’s cage then turning it on and off with a timer will provide the consistent photoperiod needed for your bird’s wellbeing.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-43045d5c pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-d404b363" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-47a70e60"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-6b1ea3c0">BIRDS LOVE LIGHT!</span></h3></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-b3634304" data-pf-type="Column"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-d074d63d pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--4 pf-c-md--4 pf-c-lg--2"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-9f5c2fb7" data-pf-type="Column"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-b37fbce0--sunconure1.jpg?v=1589320971 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-b37fbce0--sunconure1_800x1322.jpg?v=1589320971&resized 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-b37fbce0--sunconure1_400x661.jpg?v=1589320971&resized 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-67b37fbc" data-pf-type="Image2"></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--4 pf-c-md--4 pf-c-lg--8"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-2fb71a73" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-0e60e1c1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-d8c8dd7b">Even if the light is artificial and contains no UV pet birds will choose to sit under light. I hear stories on a weekly basis from customers who have purchased M&M lights about about how their parrot will go back into its cage during the day to sit under the light, how finches and canaries will sing more and how screamers will scream less.  </span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--4 pf-c-md--4 pf-c-lg--2"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-1a73d074" data-pf-type="Column"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-8b42db27--Pavilion-wlights.jpg?v=1589321511 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-8b42db27--Pavilion-wlights.jpg?v=1589321511 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-8b42db27--Pavilion-wlights_400x527.jpg?v=1589321511&resized 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-bce09d5f" data-pf-type="Image2"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-b673ec2e pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-77c7e512" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-be12dfd1"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-4230f99c">A CAGE IS HARD TO LIGHT!</span></h3></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-e512b673" data-pf-type="Column"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-4ca54bce pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--3"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-a57f6878" data-pf-type="Column"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-ce8b42db--Jennfer-4.jpg?v=1589321285 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-ce8b42db--Jennfer-4_800x800.jpg?v=1589321285&resized 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-ce8b42db--Jennfer-4_400x400.jpg?v=1589321285&resized 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-4bce8b42" data-pf-type="Image2"></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--9"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-68784ca5" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-dfd177c7"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-1cffbe12">If your bird’s only source of light is from a window across the room or from an overhead light then cage bars, play tops and toys block a lot of that light. Birds prefer bright light that is consistently bright. The best way to provide that kind of light is by adding a dedicated light, like M&M pet light, to your bird’s cage. The pictures on the back of this brochure illustrate the difference between ambient light and dedicated light.  </span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-e45d40f2 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-e8ba0a6b" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-55fa320f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-0bd0dd88">BIRD’S EYES ARE SENSITIVE TO UVB</span></h3></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-0a6be45d" data-pf-type="Column"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-9ffa3b56 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--4"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-79dff4b9" data-pf-type="Column"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-562a65fa--eyeoftheblueandyellowmacawseanmurphy.jpg?v=1589319060 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-562a65fa--eyeoftheblueandyellowmacawseanmurphy_800x534.jpg?v=1589319060&resized 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-562a65fa--eyeoftheblueandyellowmacawseanmurphy_400x267.jpg?v=1589319060&resized 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-3b562a65" data-pf-type="Image2"></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--8"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-f4b99ffa" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-320fe8ba"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-884555fa">In a report published by the Royal Society of Biological Studies a group of scientists proved that the eyes of long-lived Psittaciformes have a sensitivity to <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">UVB</span>. It is also well documented that avian vets are seeing more parrots with cataracts and blindness caused by well-meaning pet owners who have misused lights that produce <span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">UVB</span>.  </span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-d94b4576 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-1b6b0e97" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-oTLFK lcHmGL pf-c0a2840f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-0d1bb73c">ESSENTIAL BIRDLIGHTING FACTS</span></h3></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-0e97d94b" data-pf-type="Column"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-b360dcd1 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--8"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-457621a4" data-pf-type="Column"><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-cfef0b48" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-44e88d9f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-944cb6d9"><span style="font-weight: bold; font-style: italic;">Full Spectrum</span> is a word made up by a light manufacturer. It has no scientific definition and it certainly has no affect on a bird’s health because it isn’t even a thing.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-8d9f4c84"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-de8ef8c9">Independent testing labs have measured bulbs claiming to be full spectrum and proven that they are no different than a standard bulb and not even close to the spectrum of the sun.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-4c84cc96"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-ea47f09c">Artificial light produces light of a single color. The experts claim that, for health reasons, the color has to be 5600K, the color of the sun at mid day. The truth is that the sun's color is always changing from 1,000K to 15,000K and there are no health affects related to light color. Bird feathers are not plant leaves, they do not perform photosynthesis.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-4220f262"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-f88b4220">Most bulbs that claim to produce UVA and UVB do not. They are the same bulb as a $2 Walmart bulb.</span></li></ul></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--4"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-21a4b360" data-pf-type="Column"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-2a65fa96--Untitled1.jpg?v=1589319507 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-2a65fa96--Untitled1.jpg?v=1589319507 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-2a65fa96--Untitled1_400x492.jpg?v=1589319507&resized 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-16fe5b57" data-pf-type="Image2"></div></div></div><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-ad89e680 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --pf-s-xs:15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--3"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-dcd11085" data-pf-type="Column"><img sizes="(min-width: 992px) 1200px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 991px) 800px, 400px" srcset="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-ddb479df--sunconure.jpg?v=1589319014 1200w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-ddb479df--sunconure.jpg?v=1589319014 800w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0265/0085/7903/t/4/assets/pf-ddb479df--sunconure_400x687.jpg?v=1589319014&resized 400w" class="sc-qZtVr dLIPjF pf-5b5705c0" data-pf-type="Image2"></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--6 pf-c-md--6 pf-c-lg--9"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-1085ad89" data-pf-type="Column"><ul data-pf-type="List" class="sc-pcLhl bMMcvF pf-0de616fe" style="--text-indent:0; --line-spacing:10px;"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-2343ed72"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-73f351bf">No pet bird species lives in the desert and sits on a flat rock exposed to the extreme heat and sun all day. Please never use a reptile light on your bird.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-ed72ed72"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-85a32226">UVB is only present on cloudless days for a few hours per day. It is not present in the shade and it is not present all year round.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-ed72cc36"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-1d57d274">The amount of UV the sun produces varies depending on geographic location. Pet bird species are native to many parts of the world, so lighting needs are different for each species.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-cc360de6"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-5b6e2343">There is only one study performed on Parrots (African Grey) that showed significant increases in vitamin D3 when exposed to UVB. The same study claimed that similar results could be achieved via diet. The same study was repeated on Amazon Parrots with no positive result.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-oUnPI iVVzrr pf-cefc0096"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-f823cefc">While it is true that birds can see the UVA spectrum, they are not colorblind without it.</span></li></ul></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-f27d7941" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-70e0f27d pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg:15px; --pf-s-md:15px; --pf-s-sm:15px; --